bio.p:
Tomáš Kubíček(
   kubicek@brno.cas.cz
) is deputy director of the Institute for Czech Literature and a director of the Section of Narratology, Czech Academy of Sciences, Brno. He also lectures on literary theory at the faculty of arts, Charles University in Prague. He has published studies in narratology, literary theory, Czech literary structuralism, and Czech prose after 1945. He is the author ofVyprávět příběh: Naratologické kapitoly kěrománům Milana Kundery(Telling a Story: Narratological Chapters on Milan Kundera's Novels, 2002), and the coauthor and the editor in chief ofLiterární Morava(Literary Moravia, 2002) he is the editor in chief of a book seriesTheoretica.
